Vice President Mike Pence and Deputy Prime Minister Taro Aso of Japan met at the United Nations General Assembly to discuss various topics, including global and bilateral issues, people-to-people ties, cooperation in space, and the progress towards a finalized bilateral trade agreement. They emphasized the strong alliance between the US and Japan under President Trump and Prime Minister Abe, and stated that a full trade agreement will lead to greater prosperity and serve as a model for fair and reciprocal economic relations among nations.